  "prompt": "What is the average salary of IT professional having 10 years experience in India?",
  "response": "The average salary of an IT professional with 10 years of experience in India can vary significantly depending on factors such as the specific role, location, company, and skill set. However, as of recent data (2023), here is a general range:\n\n- **Average Salary:** \u20b915\u2013\u20b925 lakhs per annum (LPA).\n- **Senior Roles (e.g., Technical Lead, Architect, Manager):** \u20b920\u2013\u20b940 LPA or more.\n- **High-Demand Skills (e.g., Cloud Computing, AI/ML, Data Science):** \u20b925\u2013\u20b950 LPA or higher.\n\n### Factors Influencing Salary:\n1. **Location:** Cities like Bangalore, Pune, Hyderabad, and Gurgaon typically offer higher salaries compared to other regions.\n2. **Company:** MNCs and large IT firms tend to pay more than startups or mid-sized companies.\n3. **Skill Set:** Professionals with expertise in emerging technologies like AI, Machine Learning, Blockchain, or Cloud Computing often command higher salaries.\n4. **Certifications:** Advanced certifications (e.g., AWS, Azure, PMP) can significantly boost earning potential.\n\nThese figures are approximate and can vary based on individual circumstances.",
